From: operator-residency ablation reproduction
Subject: Name the legacy data-reconstruction kernels so the vendor SYCL accepts them

The operator-residency "OFF" variant (translated with --mpi-no-operator-resident)
falls back to the legacy gather/scatter path, which includes DataReconstructor1.h.
Two problems stop the vendor swsycl (Intel-LLVM based) from building it:

  1. Three `parallel_for(...)` launches carry NO kernel name. swsycl rejects
     unnamed lambdas ("No kernel name provided without -fsycl-unnamed-lambda").
  2. TWO different kernels share the name `class MyKernel4`. The duplicate makes
     the generated SYCL integration header emit conflicting `KernelInfoData`
     specializations ("'KernelInfoData' is not a class template"). This is the
     root cause that survives naming only the three unnamed kernels.

Fix: forward-declare five unique, template-dependent kernel-name tags and attach
one to each launch. Behavior is unchanged (a kernel name is metadata only).

Apply against the shared runtime header as an overlay (compile the OFF variant
with `-I<overlay_dir> -I<runtime>` so the patched copy wins). Do NOT edit the
shared runtime in place.

